Understand about Semantic HTML5 form elements like <label>, <fieldset>, and <legend>

1:<label>: Associates text labels with form elements for better user understanding.
2:<fieldset>: Groups related form elements together, creating a visual and semantic grouping.
3:<legend>: Provides a caption or title for the <fieldset> element. 
code: 
<fieldset>
            <legend>Personal info</legend>
            <div>
                <label for="username">Username</label>
                <input type="text" name="username">
            </div>
            <div>
                <label for="email">Email </label>
                <input type="email" 
                name="email" >
            </div>
            <div>
                <label for="password">Password</label>
                <input type="password" id="password" placeholder="password here">
             </div>   
        </fieldset>
